1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:18,800
Today we are going to talk about unwholesome mental factors.

2
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:24,700
This is from the One Hundred Dharma Structure by Bodhisattva Vasavandhu.

3
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:28,600
It talks about everything in terms of One Hundred Dharma.

4
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:34,100
Out of the One Hundred Dharma, fifty-one are mental factors.

5
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:40,800
Out of the fifty-one, there are twenty-six that are considered unwholesome mental factors.

6
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,600
So these are our afflictions.

7
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:48,100
In this class, we will talk about these twenty-six unwholesome mental factors.

8
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:51,900
Hopefully it will help us eradicate our afflictions.

9
00:00:51,900 --> 00:01:01,600
The twenty-six consists of six primary unwholesome mental factors and twenty secondary unwholesome mental factors.

10
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:08,800
Out of the twenty, it's divided up into ten minor, two medium, and eight major.

11
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:13,500
Let's first look at the six primary unwholesome mental factors.

12
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:15,700
Number one is greed.

13
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:19,200
Because we have a strong self, we are selfish.

14
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:21,500
That's why we are often greedy.

15
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:25,500
And that is the reason why we are in this reincarnation.

16
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:30,900
In the Sutra of Eight Realizations of Great Beings, it says,

17
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:34,100
Excessive desire is suffering.

18
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:41,100
Birth, death, and weariness in life originate from greed and desire.

19
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:47,200
All our life and death and reincarnation comes from our greed.

20
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:50,900
We should let go of our greed and our selfishness.

21
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:53,500
Two people were riding on the ship.

22
00:01:53,500 --> 00:02:00,100
A gave B all his luggages, trusting his friend who would take care of his luggages.

23
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:08,100
B thought, oh, I should put all my friend's luggage on the bottom, and I put my luggage on top of his.

24
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:12,100
That way, if the ship gets wet, mine will not get wet.

25
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:13,900
But there was a big storm.

26
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:20,700
So the captain ordered the crew member to throw excessive luggages into the ocean.

27
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:22,700
Four-way reduction.

28
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:25,700
All B's luggages were thrown out of the ship.

29
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:28,500
A's luggages were still okay.

30
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,300
So do not be selfish.

31
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:36,900
When you do things that are unwholesome for your own benefit, the karma will just come right back to you.

32
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:39,400
Number two is anger.

33
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:44,700
We are often angry for many different unpleasant situations.

34
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:50,500
We can be mad at our body because of birth, aging, sickness, death.

35
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:55,700
We can be mad at ourselves when we have greed, anger, ignorance.

36
00:02:55,700 --> 00:03:00,700
And we can be mad about the environment when it's hot, it's cold.

37
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:04,100
We think it's unpleasant, and we become upset.

38
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:11,300
And we can be angry about people that hurt us, our competitors, even friends and families.

39
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:17,100
And we can be angry about death at the end because we don't want it to happen.

40
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:20,700
Moreover, we are angry about ourselves.

41
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:25,500
About others, about the past, present, and future.

42
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:28,700
We can be upset about everything.

43
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:34,900
That's why we have to really look at how much anger we have inside of us.

44
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:37,500
There were two people on a boat arguing.

45
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,500
Why did you say that to me yesterday?

46
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,100
You tell me exactly why.

47
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:45,900
Little did they know, the time they spent arguing, the boat is already sinking.

48
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:50,100
The sinking boat is symbolizing reincarnation.

49
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:50,600
We are...

50
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,700
We are in the sinking boat.

51
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:57,000
But we are still quibbling, arguing, and mad at each other.

52
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,200
That's really being silly.

53
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:03,500
So do not be angry about anything or anyone.

54
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,300
Number three is ignorance.

55
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:11,700
Because we think there's a real me, we do everything dependent on the self.

56
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:13,900
That's the biggest ignorance.

57
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:16,400
And we do not believe in karma.

58
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:19,800
Doing wholesome deeds will bring good retribution.

59
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,100
And

60
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:23,800
unwholesome deeds will give you unwholesome retribution.

61
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:30,000
When we do not believe in karma, we will likely be worried and fearful about everything.

62
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,300
Because we don't understand karma.

63
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:34,100
That's all ignorance.

64
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:37,100
Number four is arrogance.

65
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:40,800
Everybody is arrogant in some ways.

66
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:47,000
Some are arrogant because of their education, their wealth, or their looks.

67
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
You might look down upon others.

68
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,800
That's all.

69
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,800
Because of our arrogance.

70
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:54,300
Number five is doubt.

71
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:57,300
We have a lot of doubt about our self.

72
00:04:57,300 --> 00:05:01,100
Doubting our ability to become a Buddha.

73
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,200
We're doubting the teacher.

74
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:05,900
We don't think the teacher has the right cultivation.

75
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:08,400
So we don't believe in the teaching.

76
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,200
And we doubt the Dharma.

77
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:14,900
We don't think the Dharma can really be applied in real life.

78
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:19,200
If we have doubt, we are constantly unsure about what to do.

79
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,900
And always confused.

80
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,800
Number six is our wrong views.

81
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:31,000
Biggest wrong view is believing this body is the real me and separate from everyone else.

82
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:36,200
That's why we have a lot of opposition with everyone else in this world.

83
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:43,200
Following the primary unwholesome thoughts comes 20 unwholesome mental factors.

84
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:46,400
Let's first look at the 10 minor ones.

85
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,300
Number one is hatred.

86
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:54,500
When unpleasant event happens, hatred can arise because of someone's words.

87
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:57,500
Because of the situation, we can explode.

