Even when you're poor, you can still be proud.

119
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:43,800
Even if you have no education, you can still think I'm very smart.

120
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,900
That's all because of our natural pride.

121
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:49,100
Number eight is harmfulness.

122
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:54,400
When we have a vaccination, we might want to cause harm to others.

123
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:59,900
We want to kill, we want to do all these things that are very violent.

124
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,700
Number nine is jealousy.

125
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:04,700
Jealousy is also anger.

126
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:12,300
We do not want to see others being successful because we think we should be the only one that should be successful.

127
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:14,700
That's because of our selfishness.

128
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,600
Number ten is parsimony.

129
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,600
Number ten is parsimony.

130
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:24,200
When we are stingy, we don't want to share our wealth or the dharma because we don't want others to have it.

131
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:29,000
All these are very strong vaccinations and afflictions.

